A series of functions for single level multivariate compositional models

Source: R/mvcoda.R
mvcoda.Rd

Fit Bayesian generalised (non-)linear multivariate compositional model via full Bayesian inference using Stan, when composition is the outcome.

Usage

mvcoda(data, formula, sbp, parts, ...)

Arguments

data

A data.frame or data.table containing data of all variables used in the analysis. It must include a composition and a ID variable. Required.

formula

A object of class brmsformula, mvbrmsformula: A symbolic description of the model to be fitted.

sbp

A signary matrix indicating sequential binary partition. Required. Details of the model specification can be found in mvbrmsformula.

parts

A character vector specifying the names of compositional variables. Required.

...

Further arguments passed to brm.

Value

A list of results. TODO

Examples

data(mcompd)
data(sbp)
## run mvcoda
mv <- mvcoda(mcompd, mvbind(ilr1, ilr2, ilr3, ilr4) ~ STRESS + Age + Female,
              sbp, c("TST", "WAKE", "MVPA", "LPA", "SB"))
